// Arms Act 1960 [Act 206] — the firearms cluster, chosen for the flagship
// negligent-discharge scenario ("shot at a squirrel on my own land, the bullet
// came down on a pedestrian") and basic gun-owner footing:
// s3 (the licence requirement — no possession/carry/use without an arms
// licence or permit granted under s4), s4 (grant/renewal — licence carries
// CONDITIONS and restrictions on its face, s4(3); expires 30 June, s4(4)),
// s8 (penalty for unlicensed possession/carrying OR breach of licence
// conditions: ≤7 years / ≤RM10,000 / both), s34 (drunk or disorderly while
// carrying an arm: ≤1 year / ≤RM1,000), s37 (CAUSING INJURY by discharge
// without lawful excuse — the squirrel section: discharging and injuring
// anyone, fatally or not, is the offence UNLESS the shooter proves lawful
// justification or that he took all reasonable precautions: ≤2 years /
// ≤RM5,000 — note the built-in reverse-onus defence), s39 (WHERE you may
// discharge at all — only at a permitted shooting range, for protection of
// life or property, under wildlife-law authorization, or as forces/police on
// duty. "My own property" is NOT on the list — the squirrel shot is already
// an offence before the bullet lands), s43 (general penalty — the s39 breach
// penalty lives here: ≤1 year / ≤RM2,000).
// AUTHORITY: PDRM — licensing runs through the Chief Police Officer of the
// State (s4) and enforcement is police. state:ALL — federal, applies
// nationwide (Sabah/Sarawak from 1977).
// EN text pdftotext-extracted from the official AGC "online version of
// updated text of reprint — As at 4 July 2023" (corpus/raw/act206/en.pdf).
// Re-derived against the 2023 text after the 2017 consolidation was
// superseded: all seven sections are word-for-word unchanged from the 2017
// text (only page layout differs); section numbers and headings unchanged.
// Layout multi-space runs collapsed to single spaces; words/punctuation/
// numbering untouched. All chunks verified:false until keeper word-for-word
// PDF check.
// Refs are one-hop legal edges (requirement→penalty, discharge→injury,
// prohibition→general penalty, AA possession→FIPA aggravated possession,
// AA s37 injury→PC negligence sections for the same facts).
// REJECTED (kept out on citizen-facing scope): s5 (restrictions on grant —
// dealer/technical), s6 (exemptions — dealers, forces, theatrical), s7 (loss
// reporting duplicates s35 ground), s32/s33 (arms in crime / unlawful purpose
// — FIPA territory), s35 (lost firearm offence — worth adding with a
// gun-owner-duties card later), s36 (imitation arms), s45 (possession
// presumption — add when a "gun found in my house" card lands), Part IV
// search/seizure powers (s47-s56 — add with a raid/search card).
{"id": "AA1960-s3-en-0", "authority": "PDRM", "statute": "Arms Act 1960", "statute_abbr": "AA 1960", "act_number": "206", "state": "ALL", "section": "3", "kind": "offence", "refs": [{"statute": "AA1960", "section": "4"}, {"statute": "AA1960", "section": "8"}], "heading": "No person to possess, carry or use arms or ammunition without an arms licence or an arms permit", "lang": "en", "text": "3. (1) Subject to this Act and any regulations made thereunder, no person shall have in his possession, custody or control any arms or ammunition unless he is the holder of an arms licence in that behalf granted to him under section 4.\n(2) Notwithstanding subsection (1), a person may carry and use arms or ammunition in accordance with the terms of a valid permit granted to him under section 4:\nProvided that there is in force an arms licence in respect of those arms and ammunition granted to some other person.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=206", "as_at": "2023-07-04", "verified": true}
{"id": "AA1960-s4-en-0", "authority": "PDRM", "statute": "Arms Act 1960", "statute_abbr": "AA 1960", "act_number": "206", "state": "ALL", "section": "4", "kind": "procedure", "refs": [{"statute": "AA1960", "section": "3"}, {"statute": "AA1960", "section": "8"}], "heading": "Grant and renewal of arms licences and arms permits", "lang": "en", "text": "4. (1) An application for an arms licence or arms permit shall be made in the prescribed form to the Chief Police Officer of the State in which the applicant resides, and shall state such particulars as may be required by the said form.\n(2) Subject to this Act and any regulations made thereunder, a Chief Police Officer may grant to an applicant an arms licence or arms permit, as the case may be, if he is satisfied that the applicant has a good reason for having in his possession, custody or control, or for carrying and using, as the case may be, the arms and ammunition in respect of which the application is made, and that he can be authorized in that behalf without danger to the public safety or the public interest.\n(3) An arms licence or arms permit shall be in such form as may be prescribed, and shall specify the conditions and restrictions subject to which it is held, the nature and number or other identification mark of the arms to which it relates and, as respects ammunition, the quantities authorized to be held at any one time thereunder, and such other matters as may be prescribed.\n(4) An arms licence or arms permit shall, unless previously revoked or cancelled, expire on 30 June next following the date of issue, but may be renewed by the Chief Police Officer of the State in which the holder resides for a further period of one year from the said 30 June, and so on, from time to time; and the provisions of this section shall apply to the renewal of an arms licence or permit as they do to the grant thereof.\n(5) The particulars of every arms licence or arms permit granted or renewed under this section shall be entered in a register to be kept by the Chief Police Officer of a State in such form and manner and at such place as may be prescribed.\n(6) If application is made for a licence in respect of any arms or ammunition not marked with letters or figures or in such other manner that the same may be readily identified, the officer to whom application is made may, before issuing the licence, cause the arms or ammunition, as the case may be, to be marked with some permanent mark whereby the same may be afterwards known and identified, but in such manner as not to injure or deface the same.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=206", "as_at": "2023-07-04", "verified": true}
{"id": "AA1960-s8-en-0", "authority": "PDRM", "statute": "Arms Act 1960", "statute_abbr": "AA 1960", "act_number": "206", "state": "ALL", "section": "8", "kind": "penalty", "refs": [{"statute": "AA1960", "section": "3"}, {"statute": "FIPA1971", "section": "8"}], "heading": "Penalty for possessing or carrying arms and ammunition without an arms licence or arms permit, etc.", "lang": "en", "text": "8. Any person who in contravention of the provisions of this Act—\n(a) has in his possession, custody or control, or carries or uses any arm or ammunition without an arms licence or arms permit in that behalf or otherwise than as authorized by the licence or permit or, in the case of ammunition, in quantities in excess of those so authorized; or\n(b) fails to comply with any condition or to observe any restriction subject to which an arms licence or arms permit is held by him,\nshall, on conviction, be liable in respect of any such contravention to imprisonment for a term not exceeding seven years or to a fine not exceeding ten thousand ringgit or to both.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=206", "as_at": "2023-07-04", "verified": true}
{"id": "AA1960-s34-en-0", "authority": "PDRM", "statute": "Arms Act 1960", "statute_abbr": "AA 1960", "act_number": "206", "state": "ALL", "section": "34", "kind": "offence", "heading": "Carrying a firearm while drunk or disorderly", "lang": "en", "text": "34. Any person who is drunk, or who behaves in a disorderly manner, while carrying an arm shall, on conviction, be liable to imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year or to a fine not exceeding one thousand ringgit or to both.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=206", "as_at": "2023-07-04", "verified": true}
{"id": "AA1960-s37-en-0", "authority": "PDRM", "statute": "Arms Act 1960", "statute_abbr": "AA 1960", "act_number": "206", "state": "ALL", "section": "37", "kind": "offence", "refs": [{"statute": "AA1960", "section": "39"}, {"statute": "PC", "section": "304A"}, {"statute": "PC", "section": "338"}], "heading": "Causing injury with an arm without lawful excuse", "lang": "en", "text": "37. Any person who discharges an arm and injures any person thereby, whether fatally or not, shall, unless he satisfies the court that he had some lawful justification or excuse for causing such injury or that he took all reasonable precautions to ensure that no person was injured by such discharge, on conviction, be liable to imprisonment for a term not exceeding two years or to a fine not exceeding five thousand ringgit or to both.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=206", "as_at": "2023-07-04", "verified": true}
{"id": "AA1960-s39-en-0", "authority": "PDRM", "statute": "Arms Act 1960", "statute_abbr": "AA 1960", "act_number": "206", "state": "ALL", "section": "39", "kind": "offence", "refs": [{"statute": "AA1960", "section": "43"}, {"statute": "AA1960", "section": "37"}], "heading": "Arms not to be discharged except at shooting range, etc.", "lang": "en", "text": "39. No person shall discharge an arm—\n(a) except at a place permitted in writing to be used as a shooting range by the Chief Police Officer of the State where the place is situated;\n(b) except for the protection of life or property;\n(c) unless he is authorized under any written law relating to the protection of wild life to shoot, kill or hunt wild animals or birds and is acting under such authorization; or\n(d) unless he is a member of the armed forces, or a police officer or other person engaged in the performance of police duties in accordance with any written law, and is acting within the course of his duty.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=206", "as_at": "2023-07-04", "verified": true}
{"id": "AA1960-s43-en-0", "authority": "PDRM", "statute": "Arms Act 1960", "statute_abbr": "AA 1960", "act_number": "206", "state": "ALL", "section": "43", "kind": "penalty", "heading": "General penalty", "lang": "en", "text": "43. Any person who contravenes or fails to comply with any provision of this Act or any regulations made thereunder, and for which no special penalty is provided, shall, on conviction, be liable to imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year or to a fine not exceeding two thousand ringgit or to both.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=206", "as_at": "2023-07-04", "verified": true}
